# Copy this file to ".env" in the same folder (backend/.env) and fill in your key.
# This is OPTIONAL — the app works fully without it (falls back to rule-based
# classification). Only add this if you want LLM-based issue classification.

GROQ_API_KEY=#Please put the API key here in the .env file you create in the backend folder
GROQ_MODEL=#Please select you GROQ. I have used llama-3.3-70b-versatile